@tscolari in order to vendor a dependency here you first have to vendor the code which actually uses it. In this case https://github.com/containers/image/pull/182.
You need to edit `hack/vendor.sh` and add a line to vendor `pkg/errors` + you need to modify the `containers/image` line to vendor from `docker-src-error-wrap` branch from `https://github.com/tscolari/image`, then run `hack/vendor.sh`.
After https://github.com/containers/image/pull/182 is merged you'll move `containers/image` back to `master`, run `hack/vendor.sh` again and this PR will be good to be reviewed and merged.
